					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lordstonefish" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2527320); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2527320&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204698" alt="LordStonefish" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2527320)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lordstonefish" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2527320); return false;" >LordStonefish</a></span> <span class="odate time_1461955045 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">29 Apr 2016 18:37</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2499998">
									

<p>In light of Djoric's final story, and TwistedGears's comment in the discussion for it that the site is waning, I can't help but see this as a eulogy for someone not dead yet.</p>
<p>Though I know the site is not going anywhere, the departures of Djoric, djkaktus and thekillerax as well as the sabbaticals of Decibelles and thedeadlymoose have been weighing heavily on me and I can't help but feel as if I jumped on the ship as it started to sink. That's just my opinion, I could be right, I could be wrong.</p>
<p>All that aside, +1.</p>
<p>EDIT: I've realized this might be construed as stirring up controversy and trouble. None meant, I was merely offering my take on the story.</p>

